summary: An Ordinance authorizing the Mayor and City Comptroller to issue Local Improvement Bonds for the improvement of Twenty-second Avenue South from Rainier Avenue to a point 120 feet south of Day Street et al in the City of Seattle, by constructing a sewer under Ordinance No. 18694, creating Local Improvement District No. 1795 prescribing the rate of interest thereon and authorizing their delivery to the contractor constructing the improvement.
